<tool id="blast_filter_fasta" name="BLAST filter FASTA file" version="0.0.1">
    <description>Divide a FASTA file based on BLAST hits</description>
    <command interpreter="python">
      blast_filter_fasta.py $blast_file $in_file $out_positive_file $out_negative_file
    </command>
    <inputs>
        <param name="blast_file" type="data" format="tabular" label="Tabular BLAST output"/> 
        <param name="in_file" type="data" format="fasta" label="BLAST query FASTA file"/> 
    </inputs>
    <outputs>
        <data name="out_positive_file" format="fasta" label="Sequences with BLAST hits" />
        <data name="out_negative_file" format="fasta" label="Sequences without BLAST hits" />
    </outputs>
    <requirements>
    </requirements>
    <tests>
    </tests>
    <help>
    
**What it does**

Takes a multi-sequence FASTA and the tabular output of running BLAST on it, and
divides the FASTA file in two: those sequence with a BLAST hit, and those without.

    </help>
</tool>
